{"cursor":"7330","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox person\n| name = Gilles Carle image = imagesize = alt = caption = birth_name =\n| birth_date = birth_place = Maniwaki, QuÃ©bec death_date = (aged 81) death_place\n| = Granby, QuÃ©bec othername = occupation = Filmmaker (Writer, Director,\n| Producer) yearsactive = 1965 - 1999 spouse = domesticpartner = ChloÃ© Sainte-\n| Marie website =\n}} 'Gilles Carle', (July 31, 1928 As fully funny, Carle had\npleasure to always give himself one year less, and to let people think wrongly\nthat he was born in 1929, \"The Year of the Big World Crash\": see on the Quebec\nFrench newspapers that many writers verified that, after his death, and\ncorrected his year of birth for 1928 and his age for 81. - Also see on\n[http://www.cinememorial.com/Acteur_detail.php?id=737 Cinememorial] the\ntranslation of what her younger daughter, Valerie Duchesne-Carle, wrote on\nTwitter: \"He was born in 1928 not in 1929. My father always missed this little\noddity.\" â November 28, 2009) was a French Canadian director, screenwriter\nand painter.\n\nCarle was born in Maniwaki, Quebec. His film [[50 ans]], celebrating the 50\nyears of the National Film Board of Canada, won the Short Film Palme d'Or at the\n1989 Cannes Film Festival.\n\nHe joined the NFB in 1960, where his credits included [[La vie heureuse de\nLÃ©opold Z]]. But after the NFB rejected several of Carle's projects, he began\nworking independently. [http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/index.cfm?Pg-\nNm=TCE&Params=A1ARTA0001406 The Canadian Encyclopedia] In 1972 Carle won\nthe Canadian Film Award for best Director for his [[The True Nature of\nBernadette]].\n\nIn 1990, he was awarded the Government of Quebec's Prix Albert-Tessier.\n In 1998, he was made an Officer of the Order of Canada. In\n2007, he was made a Grand Officer of the Ordre National du Quebec. \n\nCarle died aged 81 on November 28, 2009 of complications from Parkinson's\ndisease at the hospital in Granby, Quebec. He is survived by his son and three\ndaughters as well as his companion of 27 years, ChloÃ© Sainte-Marie. Quebec\nPremier Jean Charest described him, at his death, as one of Quebec's most\ninfluential filmmakers. [http://www.canada.com/entertainment/movie-\nguide/Gilles+Carle+hailed+immense+talent/2281765/story.html Gilles Carle hailed\nas 'immense talent'] [[The Montreal Gazette]]. Retrieved on November 29,\n2009.\n","linknr":188,"url":"Gilles_Carle","recorded":1375082946,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Gilles_Carle&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Gilles_Carle&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Maniwaki,_Qu%C3%A9bec","/wiki/Granby,_Quebec","/wiki/Writer","/wiki/Film_director","/wiki/Film_producer","/wiki/Chlo%C3%A9_Sainte-Marie","/wiki/Officer_of_the_Order_of_Canada","/wiki/National_Order_of_Quebec","#cite_note-birthyear-1","/wiki/Canada","/wiki/Maniwaki,_Quebec","/wiki/50_ans","/wiki/National_Film_Board_of_Canada","/wiki/Short_Film_Palme_d%27Or","/wiki/1989_Cannes_Film_Festival","#cite_note-festival-cannes.com-2","/wiki/La_vie_heureuse_de_L%C3%A9opold_Z","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Canadian_Film_Award","/wiki/The_True_Nature_of_Bernadette","/wiki/Prix_Albert-Tessier","#cite_note